<reference id="lcAreaShape2" xml:lang="en-us" rev="DITA1.3">
  <title><xmlelement>lcAreaShape2</xmlelement></title>
  <shortdesc>The <xmlelement>lcAreaShape2</xmlelement> element defines the shape of a linkable
    hotspot in a learning image. This element replaces the <xmlelement>lcAreaShape</xmlelement>
    element in DITA 1.2.</shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>lcAreaShape2</indexterm>
        <indexterm>learning and training elements<indexterm>lcAreaShape2</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <refbody>
    <section>
      <p>The <xmlelement>lcAreaShape2</xmlelement> element supports these values: <dl>
          <dlentry>
            <dt>rect</dt>
            <dd>Define a rectangular region. If you leave the <xmlelement>lcAreaShape2</xmlelement> element blank, this is
              assumed.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt>circle</dt>
            <dd>Define a circular region.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt>poly</dt>
            <dd>Define a polygonal region.</dd>
          </dlentry>
          <dlentry>
            <dt>default</dt>
            <dd>Indicates the entire diagram. </dd>
          </dlentry>
        </dl></p>
    </section>
    <section conref="../../common/commonNavLibraryTable.dita#contentmodel-lcAreaShape2/contains"
